'''CIDR'''

# [[w:Classless Inter-Domain Routing|Classless Inter-Domain Routing]]; normally an [[IP address]] notation such as 192.168.1.0/24 indicating a block of addresses.  The number after the [[slash]] indicates how many [[bit]]s are in the [[mask]]; bits to the ''right'' are not masked.
#:''For a clearer exmple, 192.168.1.35 and 192.168.1.252 are both valid addresses in the '''CIDR''' block 192.168.1.0/24, but 10.11.1.1 is not.''